            "id": "4580423",
            "title": "Centene beats Q1 street views",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Centene <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20489639-centene-corporation-reports-first-quarter-2026-results\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNC\" title=\"Centene Corporation\">CNC</a></span>): Q1 Non-GAAP EPS of $3.37 <span> beats by $1.24</span>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $49.94B (+7.1% Y/Y) <span> beats by $2.39B</span>.</li>\n<li>Medicaid HBR of 93.1%, reflecting continued tangible progress managing medical costs coupled with moderate flu.</li>\n<li>Medicare segment HBR of 84.9%, from outperformance in both Medicare Advantage and PDP.</li>\n<li>\n<p data-eci=\"true\">The Company is increasing its 2026 premium and service revenues guidance range by $1.0 billion to a range of $171.0 billion to $175.0 billion driven by Medicaid (vs. consensus of $188.8B). The Company is also increasing its investment and other income expectation by $50 million to $1.45 billion.</p>\n<p>The Company is updating its 2026 GAAP diluted EPS guidance floor to greater than $2.37 and its 2026 adjusted diluted EPS guidance floor to greater than $3.40. (vs. consensus of $3.02)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
